<a name="chin101"><p><b>CHIN 101 First-Year Chinese for Non-Heritage Learners (5)</b><br/>Introduction to the standard language. Emphasis on learning correct pronunciation and basic structure. Drill in oral use of the language. Open only to students who do not have any previous training in Chinese. Cannot be taken for credit in combination with CHIN 134. First in a sequence of three. Offered: A.<br/><a href="https://myplan.washington.edu/course/#/courses/CHIN101" target="_blank">View course details in MyPlan: CHIN 101</a></p></a>
