<a name="chin212"><p><b>CHIN 212 Second-Year Chinese for Heritage Learners (5) A&amp;H</b><br/>Stresses advanced grammar and vocabulary expansion. Cannot be taken for credit in combination with CHIN 234. Second in a sequence of three. Prerequisite: minimum grade of 2.0 in CHIN 211. Offered: W.<br/><a href="https://myplan.washington.edu/course/#/courses/CHIN212" target="_blank">View course details in MyPlan: CHIN 212</a></p></a>
<a name="chin213"><p><b>CHIN 213 Second-Year Chinese for Heritage Learners (5) A&amp;H</b><br/>Stresses advanced grammar and vocabulary expansion. Emphasizes reading and writing. Continues aural and oral practice. Cannot be taken for credit in combination with CHIN 234. Third in a sequence of three. Prerequisite: minimum grade of 2.0 in CHIN 212. Offered: Sp.<br/><a href="https://myplan.washington.edu/course/#/courses/CHIN213" target="_blank">View course details in MyPlan: CHIN 213</a></p></a>
